Portugal Studies Wage Cuts for Government Workers, Diario Says

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-10-12T07:25:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/portugal-studies-wage-cuts-for-government-workers-diario-says.html
The  Portuguese government  is
studying the possibility of implementing new wage cuts for
government workers in 2012, Diario Economico reported, without
saying how it obtained the information.  A decision on these new wage cuts will only be taken at a
cabinet meeting tomorrow in which the government will approve
its 2012 budget proposal, the Portuguese newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
